Drone programs are now “part and parcel” to sports coverage“What are we doing for drone coverage?”
It’s a question raised at all ESPN meetings around major sporting events, said Chris Calcinari, senior vice president of production operations for Disney media entertainment distribution.&nbsp;
“You can’t run a modern operations department without having a drone program,” said Calcinari, who added that Disney’s internal drone department will reach seven or eight full-time staffers in the near future.
